th a\\u0026nbsp;similar name.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e---------------------------------------\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eThis course is\\u0026nbsp;for the new Arduino Maker.\\u0026nbsp;\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eDo you have a \\u003cstrong\\u003epassion\\u003c/strong\\u003e for\\u0026nbsp;learning?\\u0026nbsp;\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eAre you\\u0026nbsp;excited about becoming a \\u003cstrong\\u003eMaker\\u003c/strong\\u003e with the \\u003cstrong\\u003eArduino\\u003c/strong\\u003e?\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eIf you answered \\&quot;yes!\\&quot; to both, then you are ready to get started!\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eIn making this course, I emphasized the importance of getting the \\u003cstrong\\u003ebasics right\\u003c/strong\\u003e and \\u003cstrong\\u003elearning to mastery\\u003c/strong\\u003e. As an educator for over 15 years, I know first-hand that hitting a roadblock because you lack the fundamental knowledge to progress can be demotivating.\\u0026nbsp;\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eIn \\u003cstrong\\u003eArduino Step by Step Getting Started\\u003c/strong\\u003e, I make sure that in the more than 16 hours of video content, mini projects and quizzes, we cover all the basics so that you can enjoy learning about the Arduino.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eBy the end of the course, you will have a good understanding of the capabilities of the Arduino Uno, the best Arduino for people getting started, and you will be familiar with the capabilities of several of its cousins.\\u0026nbsp;\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eYou will be comfortable with the basic prototyping tools and their usage, the basics of the Arduino programming environment, language and programming.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eYou will be able to use a variety of components. From simple buttons and LEDs, to visible color and ultraviolet light, and other environment sensors.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eApart from knowing how to use the components that I demonstrate in this course, you will also learn how to read datasheets, how to use libraries on your own, and how to learn the skills you need to create the gadgets you want, on your own. With knowledge comes freedom, and I will help you get there.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eI invite you to review the free lectures in the first section of the course to find out more details about it.\\u0026nbsp;\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003eIf you are excited about becoming a \\u003cstrong\\u003eMaker\\u003c/strong\\u003e with the Arduino, join many other Makers and me in \\u003cstrong\\u003eArduino Step by Step Getting Started\\u003c/strong\\u003e!\\u003c/p\\u003e\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eI look forward to learning with you!\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\u003c/p\\u003e&quot;,&quot;target_audiences&quot;:[&quot;Students over 10 years of age, or younger with with adult supervision. Young students should be supervised at all times when using a soldering iron.&quot;,&quot;Students with a little or no prior experience with electronics or programming.&quot;]}\">\r\n<div class=\"udlite-text-sm  styles--description--3y4KY\" data-purpose=\"course-description\">\r\n<div class=\"show-more--container--1QLmn\">\r\n<div class=\"show-more--content--isg5c show-more--with-gradient--2abmN\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div data-purpose=\"safely-set-inner-html:description:description\">\r\n<p><strong><em>UPDATED: January 2020</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>I&nbsp;have updated this course with a full new section in which you will learn how to use arrays in your Arduino sketches. This is a very useful skill to have, as you can program repetitive tasks with just a few lines of code. Enjoy!</strong></p>\r\n<p>---------------------------------------</p>\r\n<p><strong>This is the original, legendary&nbsp;Arduino course on Udemy, by Tech Explorations, fanatically supported by Dr Peter Dalmaris.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>It is trusted by thousands of students, and contains over 16 hours of content, quizzes, Github code repository, thousands of active student discussions, and countless downloadable and linked resources.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Please don\'t be confused by other courses with a&nbsp;similar name.</strong></p>\r\n<p>---------------------------------------</p>\r\n<p>This course is&nbsp;for the new Arduino Maker.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Do you have a&nbsp;<strong>passion</strong>&nbsp;for&nbsp;learning?&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Are you&nbsp;excited about becoming a&nbsp;<strong>Maker</strong>&nbsp;with the&nbsp;<strong>Arduino</strong>?</p>\r\n<p>If you answered \"yes!\" to both, then you are ready to get started!</p>\r\n<p>In making this course, I emphasized the importance of getting the&nbsp;<strong>basics right</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>learning to mastery</strong>. As an educator for over 15 years, I know first-hand that hitting a roadblock because you lack the fundamental knowledge to progress can be demotivating.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In&nbsp;<strong>Arduino Step by Step Getting Started</strong>, I make sure that in the more than 16 hours of video content, mini projects and quizzes, we cover all the basics so that you can enjoy learning about the Arduino.</p>\r\n<p>By the end of the course, you will have a good understanding of the capabilities of the Arduino Uno, the best Arduino for people getting started, and you will be familiar with the capabilities of several of its cousins.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You will be comfortable with the basic prototyping tools and their usage, the basics of the Arduino programming environment, language and programming.</p>\r\n<p>You will be able to use a variety of components. From simple buttons and LEDs, to visible color and ultraviolet light, and other environment sensors.</p>\r\n<p>Apart from knowing how to use the components that I demonstrate in this course, you will also learn how to read datasheets, how to use libraries on your own, and how to learn the skills you need to create the gadgets you want, on your own. With knowledge comes freedom, and I will help you get there.</p>\r\n<p>I invite you to review the free lectures in the first section of the course to find out more details about it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you are excited about becoming a&nbsp;<strong>Maker</strong>&nbsp;with the Arduino, join many other Makers and me in&nbsp;<strong>Arduino Step by Step Getting Started</strong>!</p>\r\n<p><strong>I look forward to learning with you!</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"styles--audience--2pZ0S\" data-purpose=\"target-audience\">\r\n<h2 class=\"udlite-heading-xl styles--audience__title--1Sob_\">Who this course is for:</h2>\r\n<ul class=\"styles--audience__list--3NCqY\">\r\n<li>Students over 10 years of age, or younger with with adult supervision. Young students should be supervised at all times when using a soldering iron.</li>\r\n<li>Students with a little or no prior experience with electronics or programming.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<button class=\"udlite-btn udlite-btn-medium udlite-btn-ghost udlite-heading-sm show-more--focusable-label--14fP5\" type=\"button\" data-css-toggle-id=\"u157-show-more--1\"><span class=\"show-more--show-less--3eSCX\">Show less</span></button></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"course-landing-page__main-content component-margin\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 4.4, 0, 2, '2021-01-14', 4, b'0', 5, 129.99, NULL, '2021-01-02');
INSERT INTO `course` VALUES (12, 'Learn Ethical Hacking From Scratch', 'Become an ethical hacker that can hack computer systems like black hat hackers and secure them like security experts.', '<div data-purpose=\"safely-set-inner-html:description:description\">\r\n<div data-purpose=\"safely-set-inner-html:description:description\">\r\n<div data-purpose=\"safely-set-inner-html:description:description\">\r\n<div data-purpose=\"safely-set-inner-html:description:description\">\r\n<div data-purpose=\"safely-set-inner-html:description:description\">\r\n<div data-purpose=\"safely-set-inner-html:description:description\">\r\n<div data-purpose=\"safely-set-inner-html:description:description\">\r\n<p><strong>The Complete Android 8.0 Oreo Developer Course by Rob Percival and Nick Walter</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Learn Android App Development with Android 8.0 Oreo by building real apps including Twitter, Instagram&nbsp;and Super Mario Run.</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>----</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>PLEASE&nbsp;NOTE:&nbsp;The most recent Android OS version is Android 11.&nbsp; If you want to learn Android 11 development, check out our brand new The Complete Android 11 Developer Course: Build AMAZING&nbsp;Apps (taught by the brilliant Mashrur Hossain).</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>----</p>\r\n<p><em>In this Oreo course I use the older Android Studio 3.0.1 version throughout as it\'s a great introduction to the development environment. For a smooth learning experience I\'d recommend you use the same as me, but students can still use the latest Android Studio version available if they prefer!</em></p>\r\n<p>----</p>\r\n<p>Wish&nbsp;<em>you&rsquo;d</em>&nbsp;thought of Whatsapp/Instagram/Google Maps?</p>\r\n<p>Me too.</p>\r\n<p>But until I work out how to build a time machine.</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s the next best thing.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>The Complete Android O Developer Course</strong></p>\r\n<p>Kicking things up a notch from my smash-hit The Complete Android N Developer Course (59,000 students + 8,500 five star ratings) -- my latest course is your fast-track, skip-the-queue ticket to building high-calibre Android apps.</p>\r\n<p>Because, let&rsquo;s face it&hellip; you&rsquo;re busy. You want results. And you don&rsquo;t have time to hang around.</p>\r\n<p>And while you wait for that big idea, developers in the US are making an average of $95,000 a year&hellip;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>&nbsp;&ldquo;Excellent instruction and content. Continuously building apps keeps me engaged and drives the lessons home nicely.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;So far it\'s a great tutorial for beginners! You learn a lot of concepts in short videos and hence it\'s not boring. You get to make a lot of apps which makes it lot more practical and interesting!&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;I\'m a senior android developer already but this course has been a huge help in revising all the basics and making the android knowledge foundation even stronger.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Why choose me?</strong></p>\r\n<p>My name&rsquo;s Rob Percival, Udemy&rsquo;s bestselling coding instructor.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>I believe that if YOU succeed, so do I.&nbsp; That&rsquo;s why for the last five years I&rsquo;ve dedicated my life to building courses that get my students coding and building apps as quickly and efficiently as possible.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>With 22 courses (and counting), and half a million students to my name - I&rsquo;ve built a multi-million dollar business helping people learn to code. I&rsquo;d love you to join my community and start seeing all the wonderful benefits coding can bring to your life, too.</p>\r\n<p>And if you don&rsquo;t like what you learn? I offer a 30-day money-back return. No questions asked.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Let&rsquo;s dig in.</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;This course was absolutely the best thing that ever happened to me. Learned literally everything I needed in android app developing. Looking forward to take other courses from Rob Percival. A special thanks to him as well for making this course. Wish I could\'ve given more than 5 STARS!&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>What&rsquo;s so good about Android 8.0 Oreo?</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Safer, smarter, more powerful and sweeter than ever!&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p>Whether you&rsquo;re looking to usher in the next generation of smart TVs, fitness wearables, games consoles, game-changing AI, smartwatches -- or just build simple apps for good old fashioned fun -- Android 8.0 Oreo is your key to unbridled creativity.</p>\r\n<p>And the potential market right now?</p>\r\n<p><strong>IS HUGE.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Play Store gives you access to a&nbsp;massive&nbsp;commercial audience with&nbsp;one active billion users&nbsp;downloading apps, last year alone.</p>\r\n<p>But, I digress.</p>\r\n<p>Fresh from Google&rsquo;s workshop, Android 8.0 Oreo is stable, feature-rich and functional as ever. Not only can you develop more efficiently, but you&rsquo;ll get new ways to extend your app.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>All you need is the right idea, or that lucky bit of exposure -- and your &lsquo;big break&rsquo; might just be around the corner&hellip;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>So join my Android 8.0 Oreo revolution today and here&rsquo;s what you&rsquo;ll get</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Learn all the new features to Android Oreo, like Adaptive Icons, Picture-in-Picture, Downloadable Fonts and Virtual Reality with Daydream.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Dive into Augmented Reality with our ARCore section. Learn how to mix the physical and digital world through a user\'s camera.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Learn essential skills like Bluetooth, game development, and sending users notifications.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>BONUS MINI COURSE</strong>: Get your free mini course on Kotlin. Kotlin is new programing language you can use in place of Java when making android apps. It&rsquo;s gaining more and more support and is a